                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1196a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-22T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>342. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 901. Your 1032, Embassy’s 378, July 17, 5 p.m. We think it best to accept the
                    British suggestions respecting the functions of the Inter-Allied Purchasing
                    Bureau in Spain, hoping that as time goes on they will find it possible to agree
                    to an extension of the bureau’s powers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
